          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Protons and deuterons were detected by",
                "scintillators and spark chambers."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detection apparatus was a coincidence",
                "spectrometer. On the basis of the known spatial",
                "resolution of the spark chambers and the reaction",
                "kinematics it was expected that a sufficient",
                "criterion to reject inelastic events for proton",
                "angles greater than 95 degrees in the laboratory",
                "would be the angular correlation of the proton and",
                "deuteron. For proton laboratory angles smaller than",
                "95 degrees selection of the deuteron by time of",
                "flight and proton energy by range were considered",
                "necessary to reduce the inelastic contributions to",
                "manageable levels."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A single CD2, target (hydrogen content less  than 2%)",
                "0.202 cm thick by 10 cm by 10 cm  was used throughout",
                "the experiment."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "As soon as the information associated with each event",
                "was placed in buffer regions of the computer memory,",
                "an attempt at geometrical reconstruction was made",
                "directly on line, allowing a check of the progress of",
                "the experiment. To avoid the need of maintaining one of",
                "the c.m. solid angles larger than the other to",
                "minimize border and resolution effects, we classified",
                "the events in bins on the proton scattering angle",
                "thetap and displayed for each of these bins the",
                "complete correlation spectrum in the sum angles",
                " (thetap+thetad). The cross section for each proton",
                "bin of width delta thetap around thetap was",
                "calculated with standard formalism."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The errors in Tables I to IV are statistical",
                "only. Possible systematic errors are as follows: (a)",
                "at a given energy, over the angular range presented,",
                "5%, this number includes 3% uncertainty in the target",
                "areal density and 4% error in efficiency; (b) from one",
                "energy to any other, 8%; the latter number includes 5%",
                "for the 12C(p,pn)11C cross-section  uncertainty, 1.5%",
                "for statistics in the monitor calibration, and 5% for",
                "uncertainties on beam characteristics reproducibility",
                "beam-spot size, position at the monitor target, and",
                "divergence."
              ]
            }
          ],
